place.name: FIVEHEAD
place.gazetteerText: FIVEHEAD, a parish in Langport district, Somerset; 4½ miles SW of Langport town and r. station. It includes the tythings of Carthanger-cam-Stowey, Moor-town, and a small portion of Burton-Pynsent; and has a post office under Taunton. Acres, 1, 721. . Real - property, with Swell, £4, 778. Rated property of F. alone, £1, 707. Pop., 489. Houses, 96. The property is much subdivided. The living is a vicarage, united with the vicarage of Swell, in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £234.* Patrons, the Dean and Chapter of Bristol. The church is ancient. with a tower; has a brass of a richly-dressed woman; and is good. There is a National school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
